text: Juan Manuel de Cañas-Trujillo and Sánchez de Madrid (n. Puerto de Santa María, Spain, July 2, 1763 - possibly in León, Nicaragua, after 1830) was a Spanish soldier, interim governor of the Province of Costa Rica (1819-1820) and subordinate political leader of the Party of Costa Rica (1820-1821). title: Juan Manuel de Cañas
